article.headline: Hawaii 92, Tulsa 62
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Michael Kuebler scored 21 points as Hawaii snapped a three-game losing streak with a 92-62 Western Athletic Conference victory over Tulsa. Julian Sensley scored 14 points Friday night and Jason Carter added 11 off the bench for the Rainbow Warriors (18-8, 10-5). Anthony Price scored 17 and Jason Parker added 12 for the Golden Hurricane (7-18, 3-12), who have yet to win a WAC road game in eight tries this season. After a relatively close first half, Hawaii started the second with a 19-4 run to put the game out of reach. Hawaii increased its lead to as many as 24 points during the run, scoring 11 straight at one point. The lead changed 13 times in the first half, the last on a 3-pointer by Carter. That ignited a 14-4 Hawaii run to close out the final three minutes of the first half as the Rainbow Warriors led 41-32 at halftime. The loss was the worst for the Golden Hurricane this season.
